1
00:00:21,070 --> 00:00:24,180
♪The breeze of the 1990s drifts by♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:27,180
♪Memories slowly flicker past♪

3
00:00:27,650 --> 00:00:31,430
♪My heartbeat
rises and falls with the tune♪

4
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:34,580
♪The story quietly begins here♪

5
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:38,640
♪Under the dim lights, our eyes meet♪

6
00:00:38,710 --> 00:00:41,850
♪Time seems to stand still♪

7
00:00:42,350 --> 00:00:45,990
♪Your smile
breaks through the clouds like sun♪

8
00:00:46,060 --> 00:00:49,150
♪Melting the snow deep in my heart♪

9
00:00:49,580 --> 00:00:53,090
♪Street posters spread signals of love♪

10
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:56,110
♪Our story slowly begins to ferment♪

11
00:00:56,800 --> 00:01:00,730
♪Hand in hand,
going through every dusk corner♪

12
00:01:00,930 --> 00:01:04,800
♪The taste of happiness is so subtle♪

13
00:01:05,480 --> 00:01:08,740
♪Crossing back to the 1990s stage♪

14
00:01:09,150 --> 00:01:12,480
♪You're my most beautiful surprise♪

15
00:01:12,790 --> 00:01:16,210
♪Love's flame burns within my heart♪

16
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:19,710
♪Not afraid of obstacles ahead♪

17
00:01:20,180 --> 00:01:23,560
♪Sway with the rhythm.
Feel your heart pound♪

18
00:01:23,660 --> 00:01:27,150
♪This love will never change♪

19
00:01:27,950 --> 00:01:35,080
♪We hold tight in this crazy era♪

20
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:40,060
♪1990s love is what we rely on♪

21
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,070
=Once More Love in 1995=

22
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:44,900
=Episode 23=

23
00:01:45,510 --> 00:01:48,950
As a company winning
both the China Food Health Award

24
00:01:48,950 --> 00:01:52,350
and the China
Food Science and Technology Award,

25
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:56,150
Jinxin always sticks
to the bottom line of food safety

26
00:01:56,150 --> 00:01:57,870
while constantly innovating.

27
00:01:57,950 --> 00:02:00,590
The concept
of healthy snacks resonates...

28
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:01,510
Stop resonating.

29
00:02:01,510 --> 00:02:02,900
Look at this photo.

30
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,380
(Zhuang Yan's Crafting of Healthy Snacks)
It's not as good-looking as me, right?

31
00:02:04,660 --> 00:02:06,350
No, you look pretty good.

32
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:08,580
Oh, winning the award is good enough.

33
00:02:08,580 --> 00:02:09,580
Enough.

34
00:02:09,790 --> 00:02:10,750
Let's take another shot.

35
00:02:20,070 --> 00:02:21,350
Before eating,

36
00:02:21,660 --> 00:02:24,350
I have one more good news to share.

37
00:02:34,790 --> 00:02:35,980
I knew you could do it.

38
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:36,630
Here.

39
00:02:36,950 --> 00:02:39,190
To celebrate our dancer's return,

40
00:02:39,510 --> 00:02:40,510
let's toast together.

41
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:42,950
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

42
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:51,237
♪Flipping to a photo from that year♪

43
00:02:53,087 --> 00:02:57,975
♪Faded smiles burning bright♪

44
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:06,612
♪I run back along the dates♪

45
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:12,225
♪Searching in the cracks of time♪

46
00:03:14,575 --> 00:03:19,450
♪If I could relive that one second♪

47
00:03:20,875 --> 00:03:26,350
♪Open an umbrella early
at the street corner♪

48
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:29,750
Yan, what's wrong?

49
00:03:31,380 --> 00:03:32,190
It's nothing.

50
00:03:33,350 --> 00:03:34,750
I just feel

51
00:03:36,275 --> 00:03:38,955
it's so good to come back to your side.

52
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:42,910
It's so good to know you all again.

53
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:47,260
It's really great to see you again.

54
00:03:48,580 --> 00:03:49,580
Where?

55
00:03:51,380 --> 00:03:52,140
Shanshan.

56
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:52,860
Mm.

57
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:53,950
I love you.

58
00:03:57,190 --> 00:03:58,190
I love you too.

59
00:03:58,275 --> 00:04:02,212
♪We didn't know
that moment was already eternal♪

60
00:04:03,312 --> 00:04:11,400
♪The counter-clockwise hand
is ultimately nailed to eternity♪

61
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,950
(Where is this?)

62
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:28,460
(Where am I?)

63
00:04:40,380 --> 00:04:42,340
Shanshan, leave her alone.

64
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:44,950
Mom, leave her alone.

65
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:49,070
Leave her alone!

66
00:04:50,580 --> 00:04:51,820
Shanshan.

67
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:53,220
How cute.

68
00:04:53,430 --> 00:04:55,110
No!

69
00:05:05,260 --> 00:05:06,950
Yan, what's wrong?

70
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:07,960
Did you have a nightmare?

71
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:14,550
Shanshan.

72
00:05:14,750 --> 00:05:15,340
Mm?

73
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:16,500
Do you like kids?

74
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,820
Why are you asking that suddenly?

75
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:18,950
Answer me first.

76
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,070
That's correct.

77
00:05:25,380 --> 00:05:27,750
Remember, kids are karmic debts.

78
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:30,340
They're the most troublesome collectors.

79
00:05:30,340 --> 00:05:31,770
Once attached,
you can't get rid of them.

80
00:05:31,780 --> 00:05:33,580
You mustn't rush to have kids,

81
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,110
nor take someone else's child.

82
00:05:35,950 --> 00:05:36,950
Yan.

83
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:38,310
Why did you say that suddenly?

84
00:05:39,870 --> 00:05:42,750
I never thought about it.

85
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:44,870
Raising kids sounds troublesome,

86
00:05:45,190 --> 00:05:47,580
but kids come into the world
because of love.

87
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:48,910
How could they be debt collectors?

88
00:05:50,990 --> 00:05:51,780
Shanshan.

89
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:53,140
Think about it again.

90
00:05:53,190 --> 00:05:55,337
The man really wants to marry you.

91
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,070
He's honest and well-off.

92
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:00,950
Marry him, and you'll have no worries
about food or money.

93
00:06:01,900 --> 00:06:03,900
Miss, thanks for your kindness.

94
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:06,070
But what about my child if I marry him?

95
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:07,630
Take her if you can.

96
00:06:07,630 --> 00:06:09,070
If not, give her away.

97
00:06:09,670 --> 00:06:11,510
Don't hate me for saying this.

98
00:06:11,990 --> 00:06:13,550
If you didn't have this child,

99
00:06:13,612 --> 00:06:15,990
this burden and debt collector...

100
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:18,140
She's my child.

101
00:06:18,140 --> 00:06:19,140
I don't feel burdened.

102
00:06:20,340 --> 00:06:21,575
Besides,

103
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:28,750
kids come into the world
because of love.

104
00:06:30,110 --> 00:06:31,780
How could they be debt collectors?

105
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:37,380
I don't care, promise me

106
00:06:37,950 --> 00:06:39,340
that no matter when,

107
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:41,550
if you see an abandoned child
on the street,

108
00:06:41,550 --> 00:06:42,500
you mustn't take them.

109
00:06:43,990 --> 00:06:44,950
Why?

110
00:06:45,110 --> 00:06:45,950
Don't ask why.

111
00:06:45,950 --> 00:06:47,125
Just do as I say.

112
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:53,950
I want you to swear to me

113
00:06:54,310 --> 00:06:57,110
you'll never give up your life
for a child.

114
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:59,070
Always put yourself first.

115
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:00,700
Love yourself, be yourself.

116
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:03,190
Don't live only as a mother.

117
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:05,780
Do you swear?

118
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:09,820
Yes.

119
00:07:10,950 --> 00:07:11,600
(Mom.)

120
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:12,990
(In this life,)

121
00:07:13,460 --> 00:07:14,870
(you must live for yourself.)

122
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:23,460
Wow, so many beautiful wedding dresses.

123
00:07:24,190 --> 00:07:26,190
Yan, you'll look amazing in one.

124
00:07:28,070 --> 00:07:28,460
Hey.

125
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:30,780
Is Qin not joining us today?

126
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:32,260
He's not important.

127
00:07:32,260 --> 00:07:33,140
You're more important.

128
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:34,660
I want to try wedding dresses with you.

129
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:36,425
Bridesmaid dresses too?

130
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:38,140
Wedding dresses.

131
00:07:39,262 --> 00:07:41,292
I want to see you as a bride.

132
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:46,070
You two are too much.

133
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:48,660
How dare you try wedding dresses
while I was away on a work trip?

134
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:49,900
Who said

135
00:07:49,900 --> 00:07:53,070
she doesn't want to mix
with people without ambition like us

136
00:07:53,070 --> 00:07:54,950
and wants to be a career woman?

137
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:57,780
Career women
can try wedding dresses too.

138
00:07:57,950 --> 00:07:59,510
We knew you were coming back today.

139
00:07:59,510 --> 00:08:00,670
We already prepared them for you.

140
00:08:00,670 --> 00:08:02,037
They're over there. Let's go.

141
00:08:10,912 --> 00:08:14,580
(Maybe no matter
how fate arranges our meeting,)

142
00:08:15,025 --> 00:08:17,055
(you'll still choose to be my mom.)

143
00:08:17,870 --> 00:08:20,510
(I'll keep becoming your child.)

144
00:08:21,262 --> 00:08:22,510
(At least this time,)

145
00:08:22,990 --> 00:08:25,670
(I pray you can have a free ending)

146
00:08:25,990 --> 00:08:28,070
(as just Zhuang Shanshan.)

147
00:08:33,390 --> 00:08:34,190
Manying.

148
00:08:37,310 --> 00:08:40,150
I saw this and thought it was pretty.

149
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:41,550
It suits you too,

150
00:08:41,950 --> 00:08:43,550
so I bought it to give to you.

151
00:08:46,550 --> 00:08:49,190
I even engraved some words on it.

152
00:08:55,910 --> 00:08:56,790
Do you like it?

153
00:08:59,190 --> 00:09:00,100
I do.

154
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,500
But why did you engrave MY?

155
00:09:03,190 --> 00:09:05,100
When I first met you,
you're called Zhuang Yan.

156
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:06,790
MY.

157
00:09:07,430 --> 00:09:07,790
Mo.

158
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:08,620
Yan.

159
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,910
It represents both our names.

160
00:09:11,520 --> 00:09:13,340
Later I found out
your name is Zhuang Manying.

161
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,190
MY is also Manying.

162
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:18,070
It's also your name.

163
00:09:24,340 --> 00:09:25,580
Help me wear it.

164
00:09:25,980 --> 00:09:26,790
Okay.

165
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:49,190
Manying.

166
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:50,700
What's wrong?

167
00:09:51,670 --> 00:09:52,670
Are you not feeling well?

168
00:09:55,190 --> 00:09:56,030
I'm fine.

169
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:56,550
I…

170
00:09:57,100 --> 00:09:58,070
I'm a little tired.

171
00:09:58,670 --> 00:09:59,580
I'll go start the car.

172
00:09:59,790 --> 00:10:00,310
Wait here.

173
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:07,220
No need.

174
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:09,310
I want to walk with you.

175
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:16,700
Okay.

176
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:17,990
I'll carry you on my back.

177
00:10:19,030 --> 00:10:19,670
Mm.

178
00:10:21,310 --> 00:10:21,670
Here.

179
00:10:35,190 --> 00:10:36,390
How strange.

180
00:10:37,190 --> 00:10:38,700
When you carried me when I was a kid,

181
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:40,740
I was always a little scared.

182
00:10:41,860 --> 00:10:44,580
Now, I feel really safe.

183
00:10:46,090 --> 00:10:47,790
Did I often carry you
when you were a kid?

184
00:10:48,550 --> 00:10:49,340
Yeah.

185
00:10:49,950 --> 00:10:52,500
Whenever I was sick or hurt,

186
00:10:52,790 --> 00:10:55,150
you'd always show up out of nowhere
like a bad omen.

187
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:58,550
Then you'd scowl and carry me home.

188
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:03,670
Tell me.
What would I look like 30 years later?

189
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:06,580
Old, poor, and ugly?

190
00:11:07,340 --> 00:11:10,580
You're not old,
but still a handsome middle-aged man.

191
00:11:13,100 --> 00:11:14,790
Just praising you makes you happy?

192
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:17,620
I'm happy

193
00:11:18,790 --> 00:11:20,460
about your bizarre time-travel.

194
00:11:21,070 --> 00:11:22,860
I'm happy to meet you in this timeline.

195
00:11:23,860 --> 00:11:25,340
I'm even happier that you worked hard

196
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,460
to reverse Shanshan's misfortune.

197
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:31,340
We changed the future 30 years from now.

198
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:35,150
I don't have to be that annoying uncle.

199
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,190
You don't have to suffer anymore.

200
00:11:40,150 --> 00:11:40,740
Qin Mo.

201
00:11:40,740 --> 00:11:41,270
Mm?

202
00:11:43,390 --> 00:11:47,580
What if one day I suddenly disappear?

203
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:57,460
Then I'll wait for you.

204
00:11:59,070 --> 00:11:59,910
For how long?

205
00:12:01,340 --> 00:12:02,150
Forever.

206
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,390
Just waiting isn't enough.

207
00:12:06,670 --> 00:12:07,980
We need a secret code.

208
00:12:08,150 --> 00:12:08,980
Secret code?

209
00:12:10,580 --> 00:12:11,390
Yes.

210
00:12:12,340 --> 00:12:14,340
If one day I suddenly disappear,

211
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:16,790
and I can't find you

212
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:19,580
or we meet again

213
00:12:19,580 --> 00:12:20,670
in another time,

214
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:24,070
our secret code
will identify each other.

215
00:12:26,312 --> 00:12:27,340
Zhuang Manying.

216
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,800
- Have you had enough?
- Have you had enough?

217
00:13:09,462 --> 00:13:10,310
(To: Qin Mo)
(Qin Mo.)

218
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:13,190
(To: Qin Mo)
(These are birthday flowers I ordered.)

219
00:13:14,070 --> 00:13:15,390
(For 28 years straight,)

220
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:18,580
(every year you'll get flowers from me.)

221
00:13:19,950 --> 00:13:21,150
(To: Qin Mo)
(If one day)

222
00:13:21,550 --> 00:13:23,150
(I suddenly return to the past,)

223
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:26,310
(let these flowers keep you company
until I grow up.)

224
00:13:26,350 --> 00:13:28,075
(To: Qin Mo)

225
00:13:28,980 --> 00:13:31,700
(There are many things
I want to do with you,)

226
00:13:32,790 --> 00:13:34,700
(but we can't do them yet.)

227
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:39,340
(I hope we can make up for them later.)

228
00:13:43,980 --> 00:13:44,790
Qin Mo.

229
00:13:45,670 --> 00:13:47,190
I'll wait for you in the future.

230
00:14:05,310 --> 00:14:07,790
First comb, comb to the end.

231
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:11,220
Second comb, you'll be together forever.

232
00:14:11,790 --> 00:14:13,950
Third comb, have plenty
of children and grandchildren.

233
00:14:15,310 --> 00:14:17,740
Fourth comb,
harmony between husband and wife.

234
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:21,100
You know these too?

235
00:14:22,860 --> 00:14:25,150
I went to a colleague's wedding.

236
00:14:25,150 --> 00:14:27,100
Her mom combed her hair this way.

237
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:28,580
The rhymes are easy to remember.

238
00:14:29,275 --> 00:14:35,450
♪Going against the wind,
landing in a spring where you are♪

239
00:14:36,070 --> 00:14:36,790
Shanshan.

240
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:37,390
Mm?

241
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:39,910
If you had a daughter,

242
00:14:41,150 --> 00:14:43,860
how would you feel
sending her off to marry?

243
00:14:44,390 --> 00:14:46,740
I'd probably feel reluctant.

244
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:48,150
Mm.

245
00:14:48,980 --> 00:14:52,340
But if she married someone she loves,

246
00:14:52,580 --> 00:14:54,580
and that person is worth trusting,

247
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:56,340
I would give her my blessing.

248
00:14:56,860 --> 00:14:58,950
She'd have
another person to love her, right?

249
00:14:59,112 --> 00:15:04,675
♪Yet crash onto an undefended island
in your eyes♪

250
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:06,580
What would you say to her?

251
00:15:09,500 --> 00:15:10,580
Mm...

252
00:15:12,460 --> 00:15:13,670
I love you.

253
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:17,980
(I love you too.)

254
00:15:18,460 --> 00:15:19,270
(Mom.)

255
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:26,525
♪Lying side by side at night,
watching the stars♪

256
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:29,100
My mom isn't by my side.

257
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,390
Shanshan.

258
00:15:32,670 --> 00:15:34,860
Could you give me away
in my mom's place?

259
00:15:34,950 --> 00:15:37,400
♪I turn my side, breathing greedily♪

260
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:38,620
Of course.

261
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:47,850
♪The faint scent of osmanthus
in your hair♪

262
00:16:58,137 --> 00:17:01,775
♪The old dial tone circles in my ear♪

263
00:17:01,900 --> 00:17:05,212
♪Faded tickets point to a cicada summer♪

264
00:17:05,375 --> 00:17:08,962
♪The videotape
whispers your image in the frame♪

265
00:17:09,262 --> 00:17:12,550
♪Against the light, the plaid shirt
reveals a clear and transparent smile♪

266
00:17:12,775 --> 00:17:16,400
♪I'm a clumsy guest in a frozen scene♪

267
00:17:16,562 --> 00:17:19,900
♪How do I answer familiar lines?♪

268
00:17:19,975 --> 00:17:23,687
♪I know
the train will leave this station♪

269
00:17:23,737 --> 00:17:27,600
♪I know the ending's in a faded future♪

270
00:17:27,662 --> 00:17:33,712
♪Yet I want to approach that warmth♪

271
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:41,625
♪Even one second rewrites missed lines♪

272
00:17:41,912 --> 00:17:46,187
♪Rewind to 1995,
back to the street we met♪

273
00:17:46,187 --> 00:17:49,487
♪Wind blows through the sycamore leaves
and lands on your shoulder♪

274
00:17:49,562 --> 00:17:53,862
♪I wish I could pause and stop time♪

275
00:17:53,925 --> 00:17:57,575
♪Let unspoken love
be preserved forever as amber♪

276
